    <div class="moz-cite-prefix">Tanvir, thought I'd add my two cents
      here.<br>
      <br>
      Rudram has two portions: Namakam and Chamakam. Namakam is
      Namskaras to Rudra the all pervading diety. A part of it says
      "spare me from you anger", thus alleviating my troubles and
      miseries. It also says "Namah Sham Bhavecha, Mayo Bhavecha, Namah
      Sham Karayacha (Shankarayacha)...", give me peace and relief. It
      is a misplaced notion to think Rudra is destroyer only.  Not to
      forget it also says "Name rudraya vishnave mrityurme pahi". <br>
      <br>
      In chamakam, we pray for Sham cha me, Sudinam cha me, Kamaschame,
      Neevara schame, Priyangu vaschame, Godhumaschame, Mudgaschame,
      .... Dhenu, ....(Give me peace, good day, fulfill my wishes,
      paddy, wheat, dals...,  It is obvious Rudraprasna being part of
      veda would not have recommended Rudra parayana/ abhisheka if Lord
      Rudra were solely a destroyer. <br>
      <br>
      Also, people do not chant Maha Mrityunjaya mantra for no reason
      when someone's life is in trouble. According to destroyer only
      notion Rudra should destroy you !!!<br>
      <br>
      I am not an expert on remedies, so please do consult a priest/
      pandit good at it. I urge you not to be mislead by "Rudra
      destroyer only" notions.<br>
