            <p>Dear Mr Tanvir,Rudra is a deity who is fiery, angry,
              tapasvi (intense long duration one pointed focus), full of
              heat, always ready to fight and destroy, take part in
              destructive wars, and finally destroy everything in this
              universe that has form. Often this power of Rudra is used
              by Maha-Vishnu in almost all avataras, to destroy tamas or
              darkness and evil forces, from time to time. For example,
              Hanuman was a Rudra-Avatara, when MahaVishnu came as Rama
              Avatara.Rudra's function is exactly opposite to Prajapati,
              The Creator of Men and Progeny. So, it will be wrong to
              say Rudra as Creator. He is not Creator, He is Destroyer.
              The very word "Rudra" means one who makes you cry.Going by
              above points, I feel in my humble opinion that Rudra's
              Anuvakas cannot be used for growth, prosperity, marriage,
              progeny etc. But yes, it can be used to destroy all evils
              in us of 6th and 8th houses, and by destruction of evil,
              perhaps we may encounter prosperity and growth, but Rudra
              cannot be directly related to growth, rather related to it
              indirectly.Yours sincerely,Nathan</p>
